parameters.description: Log of COTS intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Transformed value is approximately 0.5, representing moderate population growth potential.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m²). Transformed value is approximately 2.0, representing maximum sustainable density.
Log of COTS predation rate on fast coral (m²/individual/year). Transformed value is approximately 0.3, representing higher preference for fast-growing coral.
Log of COTS predation rate on slow coral (m²/individual/year). Transformed value is approximately 0.2, representing lower preference for slow-growing coral.
Log of fast coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Transformed value is approximately 0.8, representing rapid growth of Acropora species.
Log of slow coral intrinsic growth rate (year⁻¹). Transformed value is approximately 0.2, representing slower growth of Faviidae and Porites species.
Log of fast coral carrying capacity (%). Transformed value is approximately 50%, representing maximum potential cover for fast-growing coral.
Log of slow coral carrying capacity (%). Transformed value is approximately 40%, representing maximum potential cover for slow-growing coral.
Log of optimal temperature for COTS reproduction (°C). Transformed value is approximately 28°C, representing ideal conditions for larval development.
Log of temperature tolerance width for COTS (°C). Transformed value is approximately 2°C, representing the range of suitable temperatures.
Log of effect of larval immigration on COTS population. Transformed value is approximately 1.0, representing direct addition to population.
Log of coral cover threshold for COTS survival (%). Transformed value is approximately 5%, representing minimum coral cover needed for COTS population maintenance.
Log of competition coefficient between coral types. Transformed value is approximately 0.5, representing moderate competitive interactions.
Log of observation error SD for COTS. Transformed value is approximately 0.3, representing measurement uncertainty.
Log of observation error SD for fast coral. Transformed value is approximately 0.4, representing measurement uncertainty.
Log of observation error SD for slow coral. Transformed value is approximately 0.4, representing measurement uncertainty.
